com.revature.revabank.models

Class Account

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.revature.revabank.models.Account

  • public class Account
extends java.lang.Object
    Account holds information for a Bank Account, including the balance, the owners of the account, and the transaction history.

      • Account

        public Account(int id,
               java.util.Set<AppUser> owners,
               java.lang.String name,
               java.lang.Double balance,
               java.util.ArrayList<Transaction> history,
               AccountType type)
        Creates a populated instance of an account by transferring the values given to the internal fields.
        Parameters:
        id - an int id. This is unnecessary to populate since the database will serialize this field.
        owners - the joint owners of this account.
        name - the name the user wants to refer to this account by.
        balance - the starting balance for this account.
        history - the transaction history, if any, for this account.
        type - the account type, e.g., Checking or Saving
